 The Advertisers’ Association of Nigeria says there are new developments in its 18th annual General Meeting and marketing excellence awards scheduled to hold in Lagos. A statement signed by its Executive Secretary, Ediri Ediale said winners of the Marketing Excellence Awards will now be showcased in the directory of all World Federation of Advertisers’ member companies . The statement said another development is that entries for the awards will be assessed by International assessors as it It said also it will be hosting members’ roundtable. The statement also said that the theme for the AGM is titled, “Navigating the Nigerian Marketing Communications Regulatory Landscape.” For the Awards, the statement said the theme for the Award, “Business Value of Creativity” will witness local and international professionals sharing insights on the theme of the day, as it further said the Awards offer the ultimate platform for improving brand awareness and loyalty, by increasing the respective recipients’ prestige.” The ADVAN Awards winners are acknowledged as industry leaders and named the elite in their industry, the statement said. The event is the most prestigious and respected awards in the Nigerian marketing community, provides the opportunity for organizations to gain competitive advantage by having their projects, initiatives, contributions, products and services recognized. The ADVAN Awards is endorsed and supported by the World Federation of Advertisers, (WFA) an organization of national associations and global brands in over 65 countries of the world. ADVAN is a member of the WFA.  